      • getFixTag

        int getFixTag()
        Returns FIX tag associated with a Cameron market data field.

        See notes on getMDEntryType().

        Returns:
        int FIX tag number.

      • getMDEntryType

        char getMDEntryType()
        Returns FIX MDEntryType (FIX tag 269) associated with a Cameron market data field.

        Note that a field may map to both a FIX MDEntryType and a FIX tag. See the Market Data section of the FIX specification.

        See getFixTag() for the FIX tag associated with this MDEntryType.

        Returns:
        char Corresponding FIX MDEntryType.

      • isSecurityStatusField

        boolean isSecurityStatusField()
        Returns true if Cameron market data field corresponds to a field which appears in a FIX SecurityStatus message.

        Note that this should only be true for the key SecurityStatus fields - not the usual FIX fields that appear in many messages such as Symbol. Summary fields such as BuyVolume, HighPx etc are also excluded.

        Marking a field as a security status field in this way will result in a FIX SecurityStatus message being sent when any such field is updated.

        Returns:
        True if corresponds to FIX SecurityStatus message.

      • isSecurityDefinitionField

        boolean isSecurityDefinitionField()
        Returns true if Cameron market data field corresponds to a field which appears in a FIX SecurityDefinition message.

        Note that this should only be true for the key SecurityDefinition fields - not the usual FIX fields that appear in many messages such as Symbol. Summary fields such as BuyVolume, HighPx etc are also excluded.

        Marking a field as a security status field in this way will result in a FIX SecurityDefinition message being sent when any such field is updated.

        Returns:
        True if corresponds to FIX SecurityDefinition message.

      • isPriceField

        boolean isPriceField()
        Returns:
        true if the field is a price field
